  <static seed="87" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring650.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{2r^{4}-162}=</m> <fillin characters="27" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>2\mathopen{}\left(r-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}+9\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Once we remove the common factor of <m>2</m> the given expression is the <em>difference of squares</em> and 
we will need to make <alert>two</alert> factorizations</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
                {2r^{4}-162} \amp  = 2(({r}^2)^2-9^2)\\
                            \amp  = {2\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}-9\right)\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}+9\right)}\\
                            \amp  = {2\mathopen{}\left(r-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}+9\right)}
            \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
